						               													<description>Conflict of Alliances: Warring States &amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#231;&amp;#186;&amp;#181;&amp;#230;&amp;#168;&amp;#170;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#152;&amp;#229;&amp;#155;&amp;#189;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137; is a two player game about diplomacy and warfare in period of the Warring States in ancient China. The game begins in the year 312 BC, when state of Qin &amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#231;&amp;#167;&amp;#166;&amp;#229;&amp;#155;&amp;#189;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;had just become the most powerful state in China. The strategy of Qin is to unite the States in &amp;ldquo;horizontal alliance&amp;rdquo;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#232;&amp;#191;&amp;#158;&amp;#230;&amp;#168;&amp;#170;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;and to conquer the States in &amp;ldquo;vertical alliance&amp;rdquo;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#144;&amp;#136;&amp;#231;&amp;#186;&amp;#181;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;. In this game, one player controls the &amp;ldquo;horizontal alliance&amp;rdquo;, the other player controls the &amp;ldquo;vertical alliance&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;The game integrates diplomacy, warfare, reinforcements and initiative&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#169;&amp;#230;&amp;#151;&amp;#182;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#137;in a simple Card Driven mechanic. The game integrates diplomacy and warfare in a simple Card Driven mechanic.&amp;#10;The game places heavy emphasis on diplomatic struggle. Each state except Qin is either belongs to &amp;ldquo;horizontal alliance&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;vertical alliance&amp;rdquo; or neutral. A state in an alliance may shift to the other alliance and can be controlled by the other player during the game.        &amp;#10;The game is easy to learn and difficult to master, there are plenty of examples in the rule book and play book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
